Offensive Rating

Offensive Rating (ORTG): The number of points a team scores per 100 possessions. A higher ORTG indicates a better offense.

Defensive Rating (DRTG): The number of points a team concedes per 100 possessions. A lower DRTG indicates a better defense.

Net Rating (NRTG): A team’s offensive rating minus their defensive rating. A positive NRTG indicates that the team scores more than they concede given the same number of possessions.

Source: The Ivy League
